CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 7, 1951, pg. 15, reads: "Boxing's Cinderella Man - Jersey Joe Walcott, who'll be getting his fifth crack at the heavyweight championship of the world when he faces the current titleholder, Ezzard Charles, here at Forbes Field, July 18, is nearing peak condition for the crucial battle. The New Jersey battler is pictured going through his training paces at his camp at Rainbow Gardens, McKeesport...on the right he drives Ben Skelton, another training mate, into the ropes with a two handed attack. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Boxer "Jersey" Joe Walcott punching sparring mate Ben Skelton into ropes, in outdoor boxing ring at Rainbow Gardens, McKeesport
